				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">All this time, soloing with Rathe's Son, I've grown used to being able to handle adds and switching targets on mobs <span style="text-decoration: underline">easily</span>.
<br />

<br />
RS roots mob 1, /pet hold, /pet back off, target mob 2, engage.
<br />

<br />
Works all the time, because the rooted mob is now out of melee range and can't hit the pet.
<br />

<br />
CoW on the other hand doesn't work so well.
<br />

<br />
CoW fighting 1 mob, when a 2nd pops and aggros on me.
<br />

<br />
/pet hold, /pet back off, target 2, engage. . .  Pet immediately engages mob 1, because mob 1 is still beating on it and ignores mob 2 which is beating on ME.
<br />

<br />
Try again.  Try again.  Try again.   I'm at 40% health now, GATE. 
<br />

<br />
If I'm going to use my new improved pet, it seems I need to have a better pet discipline.  So I turned xp over to AA's again to get the new command.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
<br />
