</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Thats not true. The melee delay timer is reset to 0 everytime the pet casts, even though the spell is cast instantly. This is easily testable by looking through a log with pet attacks on and you will never see an instance where say a Water pet cast its nuke and on the same time stamp you get the next round of melee.
<br />

<br />
What you do see is that the melee round following a cast is time stamped 1 or 2 seconds later (consistent with a melee delay of 16/17). If melee delay wasn't reset you would see instances where the cast + next round occur on the same time stamp.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
