				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's incredibly easy to see that the pet casting disturbs melee.  If you watch your pet cast before it reaches a mob in melee (either when kiting or just sending your pet in from a good distance away) you'll see it physically stops in it's tracks for a split second when it casts.  Use an insta-clicky while running in an elemental form, you'll see you can still move while the animation is playing.
<br />

<br />
Or again, in a kite group, your pet will lag behind a bit after casting.  Heck, if the monster is unsnared it may even never catch up to it to melee it until it's snared.
<br />

<br />
By the way, that 0 second casting time can be interrupted too, although it's incredibly rare.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212730" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nirrudn Ak`Lmar</a>,
