			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello All.
<br />

<br />
Admittedly, I'm not a mage but have a question or two regarding Advanced Pet Discipline 1 (/pet focus), which I have had for some time but know I may not fully understand it or am not using it to it's full potential.
<br />

<br />
I'm asking here in the mage forums because back in the Luclin days when I got Pet Discipline and the /pet hold command did not work "as expected" (i.e. did not clear the pet's hate list), the problem, the reason and the solution was already completed by the mages.
<br />

<br />
Now, let's see if I understand /pet focus correctly.  I've read the in-game description and it does seem straight forward but hey, so did /pet hold.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
- default /pet focus state is unfocused when pet is made.
<br />

<br />
- /pet focus is a toggle.  Repeat command to focus and unfocus pet.
<br />

<br />
- /pet focus state does not carry through zoning.
<br />

<br />
- /pet focus state is lost (sorta obvious but have to list it) when pet dies and/or you do.
<br />

<br />
- /pet focus state is lost when pet is unsuspended.
<br />

<br />
Now if one stays in the same zone during a session, has made only one pet and pet/master don't die -- it's very straight forward: /pet focus at beginning of session and forget about it.  OR... am I misunderstanding this right off the hop?  Does the command "last" only one fight?  I'm led to believe not, because I have toggled /pet focus just to check after one or ten mobs and it'd been in the expected (focused) state.
<br />

<br />
Adding a /pet focus line into your /pet attack hotkey (not the button in the pet window) seems to be a good idea at first, but of course this isn't so because of the toggle nature.  Add that to the fact that sometimes the pet isn't specifically commanded to attack but is defending you because you got swung at, and it becomes easy to forget what state the pet is in, using the 'memory method'.
<br />

<br />
So... what do the mages do?  Toggle it on and leave it on until death/zone/unsuspend, use it only after being "needed" the first time in a session, which might be never because no adds, use a dedicated hotkey for /pet focus and use it as and when required (meaning usually the pet is in an unfocused state), or perhaps something I haven't thought of or considered?
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
