				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is a great AA.
<br />

<br />
I *do* however use the old behavior quite a bit. When splitting a camp, say bodybender/packleader in NC, with my shammy I'll enable the old behavior. That way after I  pull, I can assist with my shammy to slow the mob the pet has currently targetted, drop a heal with the mage and assist pet again with the shammy to select the other mob for slowing. In the few seconds it takes to kick off a heal, the unslowed mob grabs the pet's attention causing it to switch. That makes targetting very simple. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
